    "headline": "A Little Pressure Helped Pepsi. Can the Rest of the Food Industry Follow?",
    "summary": "PepsiCo  just pulled off something rare in the food industry: It got consumers to come back.  For the past few years, food companies raised prices so aggressively that shoppers revolted, trading down to store brands and buying less.  PepsiCo, which owns the massive Frito-Lay snacking empire, has more breathing space than most.",
